# ⏰ Cron Jobs

Cron is a time-based job scheduling service used to automate repetitive tasks.

### Basic Commands

```bash
crontab -l      # List cron jobs
crontab -e      # Edit cron jobs
crontab -r      # Remove all cron jobs
crontab filename # Install cron jobs from a file
```

---

## Cron Entry Format

```
* * * * * command
│ │ │ │ │
│ │ │ │ └── Day of Week (0-6)
│ │ │ └──── Month (1-12)
│ │ └────── Day of Month (1-31)
│ └──────── Hour (0-23)
└────────── Minute (0-59)
```

### Example

Run every Monday at 07:00

```cron
0 7 * * 1 /opt/sales/bin/weekly-report
```

---

## Redirecting Output

Run every day at 02:00 and store output in a log file.

```cron
0 2 * * * /root/backupdb > /tmp/db.log 2>&1
```

---

## More Cron Examples

Run every 15 minutes

```cron
0,15,30,45 * * * * /opt/acme/bin/15-min-check
```

or

```cron
*/15 * * * * /opt/acme/bin/15-min-check
```

Run during the first five minutes of every hour

```cron
0-4 * * * * /opt/acme/bin/first-five-mins
```

